    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2149.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">D. C. Collier</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Diego, Cal.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Responsible party here states insurrectos at Tia Juana will vacate at once and
                    end trouble on peninsula if recognized as Madero insurrectos. Otherwise railroad
                    and other property very likely will be destroyed and possibly lives sacrificed.
                    Is it possible to have Mexican minister authorize such settlement?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">D. C. Collier.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
